text=(:title Anthony Beaumont:)%0a(:table valign=top:)%0a(:cellnr colspan=3 width=380 bgcolor=#6e68a3 align=center:)%0a!!%25white%25Anthony Beaumont%25white%25%0a(:cellnr rowspan=15 width=350 align=center:) http://imageshack.us/a/img819/7268/3p8o.jpg%0a(:cellnr width=340 colspan=2 align=center:)%0a%25%25http://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/wod/headers/wodm_s.png%0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''Age: '''%0a(:cell width=190:) 32%0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''Height: '''%0a(:cell width=190:) 6'2%0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''Build: '''%0a(:cell width=190:) Fit, Lean%0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''Profession:''' %0a(:cell width=190:) Acquisitions Director, Telfair Academy%0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''Public Effects:'''%0a(:cell width=190:) %0a- Status (High Society) 2     %0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''Player:''' %0a(:cell width=190:) gothicountry%0a(:cellnr width=150 align=left:)'''Theme Music:''' %0a(:cell width=190:) [[http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BfuWXRZe9yA|Behind Blue Eyes]]%0a%0a%0a(:cellnr colspan=2 align=center:)%0ahttp://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/wod/smallsymbols/wod_s.png%0a(:tableend:)%0a%25%25http://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/wod/headers/wodm_d.png%0aTall and fit with a posture that belies a natural grace, Anthony Beaumont carries himself with an affable confidence.  His short, perfectly mussed dirty-blond hair and icy blue eyes complement a face that's handsome, but not necessarily pretty.  His clothes are designer, stylish, and expertly chosen to show off a body formed by centuries of good breeding.  His voice is strong, clear, with a hint of an aristocratic Southern accent. The very astute would place it somewhere in South Carolina or Northern Georgia.%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%0a%25%25http://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/wod/headers/wodm_h.png%0aBorn into a world of extravagant privilege and wealth, Anthony has known the finer things all his life.  But as a child, the strange paradox of being surrounded by beautiful and valuable things he wasn't supposed to touch bothered him.  Surely, such pretty and precious items should be appreciated, shared, and enjoyed?  Thus began his tumultuous relationship with the trappings of wealth and status.%0a%0a%25lfloat text-align=center margin-top=5px margin-right=15px margin-bottom=5px margin-left=0px%25http://imageshack.us/a/img690/5859/4ghp.jpg%0aHis career as a high-class thief began in his teen years, at a posh prep school in the South Carolina Lowcountry.  Lavish environs and spoiled, wealthy classmates provided a bevy of choices for young Anthony to hone his skills on.  At first, he merely stole things to take them away from undeserving owners.  But by the time he was at college at his father's prestigious alma mater, he realized that many of the things he was stealing could be sold to the right people for very tidy profits.  By the time he graduated, he was an up-and-coming talent in the black market luxury goods trade.%0a%0aAnthony spent his twenties meandering from city to city in a series of meaningless "consultant" positions, all the while focusing on his real source of income.  Over the decade, ill-gotten gains and careful investment turned a nest-egg into a modest fortune.  He grew more selective about the jobs he took.  Years of theft had honed him into a genuine authority on fine art and antiques, and some of his clients hired him to appraise potential acquisitions. Anthony was living his own, strange version of the American dream.%0a%0aHe arrived in Savannah not long ago.  Contacts in the black market alerted him to significant art and antique holdings in the old port city, and it reminded him of his home in Charleston.  Not long after arriving, he caught wind of a collection of rare and unique books in the archives at Bright Moon University.  To the right buyer, any of these could be worth a hefty sum.  With his usual aplomb, he planned the job meticulously.  But for the first time in years, he failed.  He was caught by the owner of the collection, a rather grandfatherly old man named Johnathan Potts.  Potts had the evidence and the connections to put Anthony away for a very, very long time...  but he is a man who recognizes talent when he sees it.  He made Anthony a deal, to which the surprised thief quickly agreed.%0a%0aNow, Anthony is Acquisitions Director for the Telfair Academy, Savannah's oldest and most prestigious museum, which runs three different sites packed with art and antiques. He's integrated himself among the social elites, who find him charming and respectable, a credit to the Beaumont name.  Mostly, he's a legitimate businessman now.  But when the Order of the Æternal Eye wants a manuscript or artifact and cannot obtain it through their usual channels, they turn to Brother Beaumont, who gladly provides his unique skills in service to the Order.%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%0a%25%25http://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/wod/headers/wodm_rph.png%0a'''Telfair Academy:''' Anthony is Acquisitions Director for this prestigious museum group headquartered in the historic district.  He locates, appraises, and acquires artworks, antiques, and historical artifacts to fill the numerous exhibits and gallery rooms.  Anyone with connections to the art world, museums, or history may know Anthony.%0a%0a'''Ordo Oculus Æternum:''' If there is such a thing as a typical Scribe, Anthony isn't it.  He's accumulated some respect from his fellows, and has embraced the Order's philosophy of Knowledge and its power quite enthusiastically.  Despite their misgivings, Scribes know that he's a reliable and loyal member of the Order.%0a%0a'''Old Money:''' The Beaumonts of Charleston made their fortune like so many other Southern aristocrats -- on sprawling plantations supported on the back of slave labor.  Few of those families survive today, and fewer have retained the wealth, status, and prominence of the Beaumonts. Anyone with ties to high society has likely seen Anthony at parties, gallery openings, and the like.  They may also have heard rather tawdry rumors about a scandalous, hedonistic side to the blue-blooded scion.%0a%0a'''Black Market:''' Though he's less active than he used to be, Anthony keeps his ear to the ground when it comes to the underground network of stolen goods, especially the sorts of high-ticket items he specializes in, or the unusual sort the Order desires.  Sometimes that information means dealing with unsavory types.%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%0a%25%25http://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/wod/headers/wodm_con.png%0a%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%0a%25%25http://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/wod/headers/wodm_q.png%0a''"Are we really going to stand here and debate the relative morality of necromancy versus capitalism?"'' - [[Anthony Beaumont]]%0a%0a''"He called himself my fairy godmother. In a way, that's true. Still dunno what I did to deserve it."'' - [[Heidi Morgenstern]]%0a%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%0a(:include CityBook.MortalNavigationBar:)
